1. High‑Level Project Goal
Build a per‑user One‑Class SVM (OCSVM) that authenticates mobile payment sessions based on gyroscope and accelerometer data extracted from a custom app. The system must:

Achieve ≥90% TAR (True Acceptance Rate)

Keep FAR ≤ 0.5%

Keep FRR ≤ 30%

Current baseline (with hand‑picked features and tuned hyperparameters) is ~75% TAR. The path to 90% is to systematically select the best feature subset and optimise OCSVM hyperparameters via cross‑validation.

2. Complete Data Flow
Raw JSON (data/new_raw/<user>.json) contains sessions with sensor_events, touch_events, navigation_events.

Feature Extraction (feature_creation_session.py):

SessionPipeline.run() loads a JSON, splits sessions (train/test), extracts features via SessionLevelFeatureExtractor.

Produces features/v2/<user>_training_sessions.csv and <user>_testing_sessions.csv.

Data Cleansing (Phase 1: phase1_cleansing.py):

Combines training CSVs of 13 dev users, removes duplicates, high‑missing, low‑variance, highly correlated features (Spearman, >0.95).

Outputs cleaned_features.csv (list of surviving features).

Feature Ranking (Phases 2A‑2C, using the cleaned feature list):

2A: Boruta + SHAP → boruta_shap_ranking.csv

2B: Fisher Score → fisher_ranking.csv

2C: Random Forest Leave‑One‑User‑Out → rf_louo_importance.csv

Consensus (Phase 3: phase3_consensus.py):

Weighted percentile average (Boruta 50%, RF 35%, Fisher 15%) → consensus_ranking.csv

Hyperparameter Tuning (tune_louo_expanded.py):

Leave‑One‑User‑Out cross‑validation on all available users (currently 10).

Searches nu, gamma, threshold with constraints FAR≤0.5%, FRR≤30%.

Outputs best parameters.

Final Model (train_session.py):

Uses the chosen feature set (via drop_cols) and the best hyperparameters.

Trains per‑user OCSVM, evaluates, saves models.

