5. Training Script (SessionOCSVM in train_session.py)
Feature selection: Controlled by drop_cols list inside load_and_prepare_data. Any column not in drop_cols is used as a feature.

Data loading: Reads CSV, finds label column (tries session_label, label, test_type), normalises to genuine/impostor, maps to 1/-1.

Scaling: StandardScaler fitted on training data only.

Model: OneClassSVM(kernel='rbf', nu=..., gamma=...).

Evaluation: Uses a threshold (currently -0.3). FRR = fraction of genuine with score < threshold; FAR = fraction of impostor with score ≥ threshold; TAR = 1‑FRR; Accuracy = correct / total.

Validation: validate() method exists (not called in main) that splits genuine data 80/20 and checks FRR on the 20% hold‑out. Use to detect overfitting.

Saving: Models and scalers saved to models/ directory with joblib.

